HEADWORD: Kenyapithecus
<hw>Kenyapithecus</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A genus of extinct
primates having powerful chewing muscles along with large molars and
small incisors; its fossils were found in Maboko in
<country>Kenya</country>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Kenyapithecus</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
